  "topic": "Mole Concept",
  "question": "How many atoms are in 2 moles of carbon?",
  "options": {
    "A": "6.02 \u00d7 10\u00b2\u00b2",
    "B": "1.204 \u00d7 10\u00b2\u2074",
    "C": "3.01 \u00d7 10\u00b2\u00b3",
    "D": "6.02 \u00d7 10\u00b2\u00b3"
  },
  "answer": "B",
  "explanation": "Number of atoms = moles \u00d7 Avogadro's number = 2 \u00d7 6.02 \u00d7 10\u00b2\u00b3 = 1.204 \u00d7 10\u00b2\u2074 atoms"
}